==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the [[astronomer]] Johannes Hevelius in 1687. From {{L.}} ''[[canes#Latin|canes]] [[venatici]]'', the "dogs of hunting"

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''[[canes#Latin|Canes]] [[venatici#Latin|Venatici]]'''

#{{constellation}}: A dim [[spring]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble a [[pair]] of [[hunting]] [[dogs]] (Chara and Asterion) held on a leash by [[Boötes]] and following the [[bear]] [[Ursa Major]].

